problem_prompt:
Approach the following question the way someone with a PhD in biology would. What is the molecular formula of 1-methoxy-3-(4-methylpiperidin-3-yl)oxypropan-2-ol?
Answer:
gpt_response:
The molecular formula of 1-methoxy-3-(4-methylpiperidin-3-yl)oxypropan-2-ol can be determined by first identifying the individual functional groups and substituents present in the molecule. In this case, the molecule contains a methoxy group (-OCH3), a hydroxyl group (-OH), a propyl group (-3C), and a piperidine ring (-C5H10N).

Taking into account the connectivity of these functional groups and substituents, the molecular formula of 1-methoxy-3-(4-methylpiperidin-3-yl)oxypropan-2-ol can be written as C14H27NO3.
